.TH HSH 1 "April 2024" "version 1.0"

.SH NAME
.B hsh
- a simple UNIX command line interpreter in C

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Hsh
is a basic UNIX command-line shell written in C. It provides a minimalistic shell environment where users can execute commands entered from the terminal.

.PP
The shell reads commands from the standard input, executes them, and prints the output to the standard output. It supports basic shell functionalities such as executing external commands, handling input/output redirection, and managing environment variables.

.PP
The shell supports interactive mode, where it displays a prompt to the user and waits for input. It also supports non-interactive mode, where it executes commands from a script file.

.SH OPTIONS
.B None

.SH COMMANDS
The shell supports the following built-in commands:

.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.PP
All other commands are executed as external commands.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns 0 upon successful execution and non-zero values on failure.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bash (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2),
.BR waitpid (2),
.BR getenv (3),
.BR access (2)

